Executive Assistant
The Recruitment Tree
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 6 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Our client, a well known and successful organisation internationally are looking to appoint an Executive Assistant for their CEO.
The organisation is an international service company which combines commercial know-how with a deep public service ethos. They improve services by managing people, processes, technology and assets more effectively. They advise policy makers, design innovative solutions, integrate systems and - most of all - deliver to the public.
REQUIREMENTS
Skills & Experience required include:
- Executive PA experience
- Strong interpersonal skills; able to develop strong working relationships both internally and externally - regular contacts will include divisional Directors, Group plc Board, Executive Committee, and key business advisors
- High level of organisation skills, including complex event, diary and meeting management
- Excellent communication skills - both written and verbal
- Initiative and problem solving ability
- Flexibility and adaptability; able to travel overseas
- Advanced Microsoft Office skills, particularly Word, PowerPoint and Excel, SAP desirable
- Professional demeanour and interpersonal skills to develop strong working relationships
- Excellent organisation skills and ability to plan business events, including experience of liaising with external service providers and formally managing all related correspondence and finances
- Ability to work under pressure and to tight deadlines; ability to work on own initiative, independently and as part of a team
- Experience of project managing events.
Personal Characteristics - Absolute integrity
ABOUT THE COMPANY
The Recruitment Tree is an independently owned search and selection consultancy based in the North East with offices in the Middle East.
We are experts in our specialist sectors and have access to the highest calibre candidates due to our strong long term relationships and unrivaled market knowledge. Our friendly and supportive consultants work tirelessly to meet your needs by building meaningful, long-term relationships who understand your business requirements.
If you are looking for a job, our knowledgeable consultants are up to date and well informed about the current job market and how best to find you a job you are most suited to. We will dedicate time in understanding your needs, getting to know you, and finding you the right job.
At The Recruitment Tree we strive to enable our candidates to walk away having found their perfect role, and our clients to walk away having added value to their business with their most important asset, their people.
